        "level": 2,
        "title": "Stage 1: Prep and Normalization (<code>/folio:prep</code>)",
        "text": "<p>Raw materials are scanned, classified, and normalized into structured canonical inputs:</p> <ul> <li><code>inputs/idea.md</code> — Core contribution and research questions</li> <li><code>inputs/experimental_log.md</code> — Experiments, results, observations</li> <li><code>inputs/materials_manifest.json</code> — Per-file inventory with relevance signals</li> <li><code>inputs/venue_profile.md</code> — Target outlet, format, audience, evaluation criteria</li> <li><code>inputs/figures_manifest.json</code> — Existing and planned figures</li> </ul> <p>The prep pipeline runs four scripts in order:</p> <pre><code>cd plugins/folio &amp;&amp; python scripts/prep_materials.py workspace/\ncd plugins/folio &amp;&amp; python scripts/classify_materials.py workspace/\ncd plugins/folio &amp;&amp; python scripts/route_mode.py workspace/\ncd plugins/folio &amp;&amp; python scripts/validate_inputs.py workspace/\n</code></pre> <p>Gaps in materials are marked with <code>&lt;!-- GAP: description --&gt;</code> rather than blocked. Only gaps that block the next gate require user input.</p> <p>Gate A — Input completeness: <code>validate_inputs.py</code> must exit 0 before leaving Stage 1. Errors block; warnings are informational.</p>",
        "path": [],
        "tags": []
      },
      {
        "location": "human-checkpoint-1",
        "level": 3,
        "title": "Human Checkpoint 1",
        "text": "<p>Folio presents what was synthesized, what was copied verbatim, identified gaps, and the mode recommendation. Explicit approval required before routing.</p>",
        "path": [],
        "tags": []
      },
      {
        "location": "routing-checkpoint",
        "level": 2,
        "title": "Routing checkpoint",
        "text": "<p>After Checkpoint 1 approval, Folio reads <code>route.json</code> and presents:</p> <pre><code>Recommended mode: &lt;white_paper | research_paper | hybrid&gt; (confidence: X.XX)\nReasons: [bullet list]\n</code></pre> <p>You can accept the recommendation or override it. The selected mode is logged in <code>logs/checkpoints.md</code>. Folio does not proceed into mode-specific stages until you confirm.</p> <p>Low-confidence routing</p> <p>If <code>route_mode.py</code> reports confidence below 0.5, the materials are ambiguous. Folio will ask you to choose a mode explicitly rather than guessing.</p>",
        "path": [],
        "tags": []
      },
      {
        "location": "mode-specific-stages-25-folioplan-foliosupport-foliodraft-folioreview",
        "level": 2,
        "title": "Mode-specific stages (2–5) (<code>/folio:plan</code>, <code>/folio:support</code>, <code>/folio:draft</code>, <code>/folio:review</code>)",
        "text": "<p>After routing confirmation, Folio follows one of three branches. See the mode guides for full detail:</p> <ul> <li>White Paper Mode — Perspectives, argument structure, Markdown draft, executive outputs</li> <li>Research Paper Mode — Global planning, support artifacts, LaTeX draft, finalize</li> <li>Hybrid Mode — Conceptual framing + evidence support, merged draft, dual review</li> </ul> <p>All three branches share the same quality gates (G: review non-regression) and the IP gate before review is considered complete.</p>",
        "path": [],
        "tags": []
      },
      {
        "location": "human-checkpoint-2",
        "level": 2,
        "title": "Human Checkpoint 2",
        "text": "<p>Checkpoint 2 occurs after planning in research paper and hybrid modes, or at the planning approval point in white paper mode. Folio presents:</p> <ul> <li>Outline and narrative arc</li> <li>Claim ledger summary (highlights weak and unsupported claims)</li> <li>Figure and literature plans</li> </ul> <p>Explicit approval required before drafting.</p>",
        "path": [],
        "tags": []
      },
      {
        "location": "ip-scanning-all-modes",
        "level": 2,
        "title": "IP scanning (all modes)",
        "text": "<p>Before any mode marks its review stage complete, Folio runs:</p> <pre><code>cd plugins/folio &amp;&amp; python scripts/scan_redlines.py workspace/\n</code></pre> <p>This checks all draft content against <code>ip_policy.json</code>. If violations are found, the IP Gate blocks shipping until you redact, rewrite, or explicitly acknowledge the risk (which is logged).</p> <p>See IP Policy for configuration.</p>",
        "path": [],
        "tags": []
      },
      {
        "location": "human-checkpoint-3",
        "level": 2,
        "title": "Human Checkpoint 3",
        "text": "<p>Before final packaging, Folio presents the final scorecard, deferred issues, and softened claims. Explicit approval required before export.</p>",
        "path": [],
        "tags": []
      },
      {
        "location": "final-packaging-folioexport",
        "level": 2,
        "title": "Final Packaging (<code>/folio:export</code>)",
        "text": "<p>After Checkpoint 3:</p> <pre><code>cd plugins/folio &amp;&amp; python scripts/package_exports.py workspace/\n</code></pre> <p>This assembles a mode-appropriate bundle under <code>final/</code> (and/or <code>exports/</code>). Folio reports:</p> <ul> <li>Absolute workspace path</li> <li>All artifacts produced, organized by directory</li> <li>Final review score (<code>overall</code> from latest scorecard)</li> <li>Known issues and deferred items</li> <li>Recommended next steps</li> </ul>",
        "path": [],
        "tags": []
      },
      {
        "location": "resuming-a-workspace",
        "level": 2,
        "title": "Resuming a workspace",
        "text": "<p>Re-invoke <code>/folio</code> on an existing workspace path. Folio reads <code>logs/checkpoints.md</code> to detect the last completed stage and offers to resume from the next one.</p> <p>You can also run a specific stage directly with its standalone command:</p> <pre><code>/folio:review workspace/\n</code></pre> <p>Use <code>/folio:status workspace/</code> to see which stages are complete before jumping in.</p> <p>To change mode on an existing workspace, ask Folio to update <code>route.json</code> with a <code>user_override</code> — the change is logged.</p>",
        "path": [],
        "tags": []
      },
      {
        "location": "logging",
        "level": 2,
        "title": "Logging",
        "text": "<p>Every session appends to two log files in <code>workspace/logs/</code>:</p> <ul> <li><code>run_log.md</code> — Decisions, overrides, tool failures, user waivers</li> <li><code>checkpoints.md</code> — Table of stage completions and human approvals</li> </ul> <p>These logs enable deterministic resume and provide an audit trail for \"why did we ship this draft?\"</p>",
        "path": [],
        "tags": []
      },
      {
        "location": "workspace-layout",
        "level": 2,
        "title": "Workspace layout",
        "text": "<pre><code>workspace/\n  intent.json\n  route.json\n  ip_policy.json\n  inputs/\n    raw_materials/\n    idea.md\n    experimental_log.md\n    venue_profile.md\n    materials_manifest.json\n    figures_manifest.json\n  planning/\n    outline.json\n    claim_ledger.json\n    figure_plan.json\n    literature_plan.json\n    results_inventory.json\n    perspectives.json        (white paper / hybrid)\n    question_tree.json       (white paper / hybrid)\n    argument_graph.md        (white paper / hybrid)\n  citations/\n    citation_pool.json\n    refs.bib\n  figures/\n    generated/\n    supplied/\n    captions.json\n  tables/\n    generated/\n  drafts/\n    paper.tex                (research paper / hybrid LaTeX)\n    paper.md                 (white paper / hybrid Markdown)\n    sections/\n  reviews/\n    review_round_N.md\n    scorecard.json\n    ip_safety_report.md\n  final/\n    paper.tex\n    paper.pdf\n    refs.bib\n    figures/\n  exports/\n    executive_summary.md     (white paper / hybrid)\n    bd_talking_points.md     (white paper / hybrid)\n  logs/\n    run_log.md\n    checkpoints.md\n</code></pre> <p>See Artifacts for a stage-by-stage breakdown of what each artifact is and when it is created.</p>",
        "path": [],
        "tags": []
      }
    ],
